article.headline: Oregon 78, UCLA 71
article.story:
EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Brandi Davis came off the bench to score a
game high 28 points and Corrie Mizusawa added 11 as Oregon defeated
UCLA 78-71 on Thursday.

Lisa Willis led the Bruins with 24 points and six rebounds,
while Amanda Livingston and Nikki Blue scored 15 each.

Oregon (13-6, 6-4 Pac-10) used a 15-2 run midway through the
second half to build a 58-48 lead. Davis had two 3-pointers, a
steal and a lay-up during in the spurt as the Ducks took the lead
for good.

The Bruins (12-7, 6-4) cut the advantage to 70-66 with three
minutes remaining, but the Ducks held on despite missing six of 14
free throws in the final minutes.

The Ducks dominated the Bruins on the boards, outrebounding them
50-30. UCLA, however, collected 11 steals to keep the game close.

Oregon trailed by as many as nine in the first half before
taking a 33-31 lead into the break.
